review_blob:
Berlin Beer Fest. A West Coast IPA which could also be considered as a double IPA. Though 6,6 abv arent enough to be mentioned like this :)
Nice Color, golden orange, small head. Lots of tropical fruityness in my nose. Hoppy flavors and a decent malty sweetness. Long Lasting aftertaste. Congratulations.
Berlin Beer Fest. Good Double IPA with fruity and grassy notes and moderate maltiness. Full bodied with a long aftertaste. Nice labeling.
Nice and dark full bodied beer with sweet Aromas of caramel and dark fruit. Typical belgian.
Nice Color, nice head. Floral and fruity hop Aromas in the nose. Malty and fruity flavors like Lemon and peach. Great and Long aftertaste.
Cask, small white head, hoppy nose, fruity exotic aromas. Thin Body but a sweet maltiness with nice citruslike flavors. Good aftertaste.
beer_name: Bankss / Green Flash Citra Session IPA
